header.description: Clients need to specify Authorization or X-DD-AUTH-TOKEN.
Clients need to specify Authorization or X-DD-AUTH-TOKEN.

query.description: page number, starting from 0
Paging size
sort="collection_epoch,app_pool_name,system_name,site_name". Default is descending order. For descending order, prefix the key with a dash (-). Ex: -collection_epoch

filter="collection_epoch=regex and app_pool_name=regex and system_name=regex and site_name=regex and app_pool_uuid= regex and system_uuid=regex and site_uuid= regex and tier=value" collection_epoch=regex  Collection_epoch can not be repeated. Value should be a range, eg (start_time, end_time). Start time for historical data, unit is epoch time. Default value is '0', returns all historical data for requested interval or sample of minimal unit in db. End time for historical data, unit is epoch time. Default value is current epoch time. tier=value where value can be 'total', 'active' or 'cloud'. Default is active.
Unit for sample data. ex: hour, day, week. Default value is minimal unit database keeps for this historical data.
Comma separated list of fields to be excluded from response object. Required and general fields such as paging will not be excluded. For example, "msg, status,severity" for an alert.
